cards.name: The Fool
cards.description: An image prompt for The Fool card: A person standing at the edge of a cliff, holding a small bag, and looking towards the horizon with a sense of adventure.
cards.interpretation: The Fool represents new beginnings, spontaneity, and embracing the unknown. It signifies taking risks and trusting in the journey ahead. This card encourages you to follow your instincts and explore uncharted territory.

cards.name: The Magician
cards.description: An image prompt for The Magician card: A person in a robe standing behind a table adorned with various objects, one hand pointing towards the sky and the other towards the ground.
cards.interpretation: The Magician symbolizes manifestation, creativity, and personal power. It signifies the ability to harness your skills and resources to bring about change. This card reminds you of your potential and encourages you to take action to achieve your goals.

cards.name: The High Priestess
cards.description: An image prompt for The High Priestess card: A woman seated on a throne, holding a book in her lap, and a crescent moon at her feet.
cards.interpretation: The High Priestess represents intuition, mystery, and inner wisdom. It signifies a deep connection to your subconscious mind and the hidden aspects of life. This card encourages you to listen to your inner voice and trust your intuition in making decisions.

cards.name: The Empress
cards.description: An image prompt for The Empress card: A pregnant woman seated on a throne surrounded by lush vegetation and a flowing river.
cards.interpretation: The Empress symbolizes abundance, nurturing, and creativity. It signifies the power of nature and the ability to create and nurture life. This card represents fertility, growth, and the flourishing of ideas and projects.

cards.name: The Emperor
cards.description: An image prompt for The Emperor card: A person seated on a throne, wearing a crown and holding a scepter, representing authority and stability.
cards.interpretation: The Emperor represents authority, structure, and leadership. It signifies the ability to take control of a situation and establish order. This card reminds you to assert yourself with confidence and take charge of your life.

cards.name: The Hierophant
cards.description: An image prompt for The Hierophant card: A religious figure seated on a throne, holding a staff and a scroll, representing tradition and spirituality.
cards.interpretation: The Hierophant symbolizes tradition, spirituality, and guidance. It signifies seeking wisdom from established institutions and adhering to conventional beliefs. This card encourages you to seek mentorship and spiritual guidance to find meaning and purpose.

cards.name: The Lovers
cards.description: An image prompt for The Lovers card: Two people standing together, surrounded by an angel above them, representing love, harmony, and choices.
cards.interpretation: The Lovers represent love, harmony, and partnerships. It signifies choices and the need to align your values with your relationships. This card encourages you to make decisions from a place of love and deep connection.

cards.name: The Chariot
cards.description: An image prompt for The Chariot card: A person riding a chariot, pulled by two opposing forces, representing determination and willpower.
cards.interpretation: The Chariot represents determination, willpower, and overcoming obstacles. It signifies a journey towards success and victory. This card reminds you to stay focused, take control of your life, and overcome challenges through sheer determination.

cards.name: Strength
cards.description: An image prompt for the Strength card: A person holding open the jaws of a lion, representing courage and inner strength.
cards.interpretation: Strength represents courage, resilience, and inner strength. It signifies the power to overcome challenges through compassion and self-control. This card reminds you to embrace your inner strength and face difficulties with grace.

cards.name: The Hermit
cards.description: An image prompt for The Hermit card: A person standing alone on a mountaintop, holding a lantern, symbolizing solitude and introspection.
cards.interpretation: The Hermit represents solitude, introspection, and inner guidance. It signifies the need for introspection and seeking answers within yourself. This card encourages you to withdraw from the noise of the world and listen to your inner voice.

cards.name: Wheel of Fortune
cards.description: An image prompt for the Wheel of Fortune card: A large wheel turning with figures representing the cycle of life and destiny.
cards.interpretation: The Wheel of Fortune symbolizes destiny, cycles, and change. It signifies the ups and downs of life and the ever-changing circumstances. This card reminds you that life is full of both good and bad times and encourages you to embrace the changes that come your way.

cards.name: Justice
cards.description: An image prompt for the Justice card: A person holding a scale, representing balance, fairness, and truth.
cards.interpretation: Justice represents fairness, balance, and truth. It signifies the need to make decisions based on reason and fairness. This card reminds you to seek truth and consider the consequences of your actions before making judgments.

cards.name: The Hanged Man
cards.description: An image prompt for The Hanged Man card: A person suspended upside down from a tree, symbolizing surrender and new perspectives.
cards.interpretation: The Hanged Man represents surrender, letting go, and gaining new perspectives. It signifies a need to pause, reflect, and change your approach. This card encourages you to let go of control and find a fresh outlook on a situation.

cards.name: Death
cards.description: An image prompt for the Death card: A skeleton figure, often riding a horse, representing transformation and new beginnings.
cards.interpretation: Death symbolizes transformation, endings, and new beginnings. It signifies the need to let go of the old to make way for the new. This card reminds you that change is inevitable and necessary for growth and renewal.

cards.name: Temperance
cards.description: An image prompt for the Temperance card: A person pouring water between two cups, symbolizing balance, moderation, and harmony.
cards.interpretation: Temperance represents balance, harmony, and moderation. It signifies the need to find a middle ground and integrate opposing forces. This card reminds you to seek balance in your life and maintain a harmonious approach to all aspects.

cards.name: The Devil
cards.description: An image prompt for The Devil card: A devil figure, often depicted with horns and chains, representing temptation, materialism, and unhealthy attachments.
cards.interpretation: The Devil symbolizes temptation, materialism, and unhealthy attachments. It signifies the need to break free from limiting beliefs and destructive patterns. This card warns against giving in to negative influences and encourages you to reclaim your power.

cards.name: The Tower
cards.description: An image prompt for The Tower card: A tower struck by lightning, often with people falling from it, representing sudden change and upheaval.
cards.interpretation: The Tower represents sudden change, upheaval, and revelations. It signifies the breaking down of old structures and beliefs to make way for something new. This card reminds you that sometimes destruction is necessary for growth and transformation.

cards.name: The Star
cards.description: An image prompt for The Star card: A person kneeling by a water source, often pouring water and surrounded by stars, symbolizing hope, inspiration, and guidance.
cards.interpretation: The Star represents hope, inspiration, and guidance. It signifies a sense of renewal and the promise of a bright future. This card reminds you to trust in the universe and believe in your dreams.

cards.name: The Moon
cards.description: An image prompt for The Moon card: A moon in the night sky with a dog and a wolf howling, symbolizing intuition, the subconscious mind, and illusions.
cards.interpretation: The Moon represents intuition, the subconscious mind, and illusions. It signifies the need to trust your instincts and navigate the unknown. This card warns against being deceived by illusions and encourages you to explore your deepest desires and fears.

cards.name: The Sun
cards.description: An image prompt for The Sun card: A radiant sun with a smiling face, often depicted above joyful figures, representing success, happiness, and vitality.
cards.interpretation: The Sun represents success, happiness, and vitality. It signifies a period of joy, abundance, and optimism. This card reminds you to embrace the light within you and enjoy the blessings in your life.

cards.name: Judgment

cards.interpretation: Judgment represents rebirth, awakening, and self-reflection. It signifies a call to evaluate your past actions and make amends. This card encourages you to release judgment and embrace forgiveness to move forward with clarity and renewal.

cards.name: The World

cards.interpretation: The World represents completion, fulfillment, and wholeness. It signifies a sense of accomplishment and reaching a state of harmony. This card reminds you that you have come full circle and encourages you to celebrate your achievements.

cards.name: Ace of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Ace of Wands represents inspiration, new opportunities, and potential. It signifies the beginning of a creative or passionate endeavor. This card encourages you to seize the opportunities that come your way and channel your energy into fruitful ventures.

cards.name: Two of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Two of Wands represents planning, vision, and personal power. It signifies the need to make decisions and take action based on a long-term vision. This card reminds you to trust in your abilities and take charge of your own destiny.

cards.name: Three of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Three of Wands represents exploration, enterprise, and expansion. It signifies the need to venture outside your comfort zone and embrace new opportunities. This card encourages you to have confidence in your abilities and explore uncharted territories.

cards.name: Four of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Four of Wands represents joy, harmony, and stability. It signifies a time of celebration and the fulfillment of goals. This card reminds you to appreciate the harmony and abundance in your life and celebrate your achievements.

cards.name: Five of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Five of Wands represents competition, conflict, and challenges. It signifies the need to overcome obstacles and find solutions in a situation of conflict. This card reminds you to embrace healthy competition and collaborate to find a way forward.

cards.name: Six of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Six of Wands represents victory, recognition, and public acclaim. It signifies a time of achievement and success. This card reminds you to take pride in your accomplishments and embrace the recognition you receive.

cards.name: Seven of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Seven of Wands represents perseverance, defensiveness, and resilience. It signifies the need to stand your ground and protect your position. This card reminds you to have confidence in your abilities and face challenges with determination.

cards.name: Eight of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Eight of Wands represents swift action, progress, and movement. It signifies a period of rapid change and forward momentum. This card encourages you to seize the opportunities that come your way and take decisive action.

cards.name: Nine of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Nine of Wands represents resilience, courage, and persistence. It signifies the need to stay strong and resilient despite challenges. This card reminds you to keep pushing forward and trust in your abilities to overcome obstacles.

cards.name: Ten of Wands
cards.description: An image prompt for the Ten of Wands card: A person carrying a heavy burden of ten wands, often depicted in a stooped or overwhelmed posture, representing responsibility, burdens, and hard work.
cards.interpretation: The Ten of Wands represents responsibility, burdens, and hard work. It signifies a time of carrying heavy loads and feeling overwhelmed. This card reminds you to assess your responsibilities and seek support if needed to lighten your load.

cards.name: Page of Wands
cards.description: An image prompt for the Page of Wands card: A youthful figure holding a wand, often with a curious or adventurous expression, representing enthusiasm, exploration, and new beginnings.
cards.interpretation: The Page of Wands represents enthusiasm, exploration, and new beginnings. It signifies the arrival of exciting opportunities and the need to embrace a spirit of curiosity. This card encourages you to approach new ventures with a sense of adventure.

cards.name: Knight of Wands
cards.description: An image prompt for the Knight of Wands card: A knight figure on a horse, often with a wand, in a dynamic or charging pose, representing action, passion, and adventure.
cards.interpretation: The Knight of Wands represents action, passion, and adventure. It signifies a period of dynamic energy and the pursuit of your goals with determination. This card encourages you to embrace your passions and take bold steps towards your dreams.

cards.name: Queen of Wands

cards.interpretation: The Queen of Wands represents creativity, leadership, and confidence. It signifies a time of self-assurance and the ability to inspire others. This card reminds you to trust your instincts and embrace your personal power.

cards.name: King of Wands

cards.interpretation: The King of Wands represents vision, strength, and charisma. It signifies a time of confident leadership and the ability to bring your visions to life. This card reminds you to trust in your abilities and use your personal power wisely.

cards.name: Ace of Cups

cards.interpretation: The Ace of Cups represents love, emotional abundance, and new beginnings. It signifies the start of a deep emotional connection or the awakening of love within you. This card encourages you to open your heart and embrace the love and compassion that surrounds you.

cards.name: Two of Cups

cards.interpretation: The Two of Cups represents partnership, connection, and harmony. It signifies the coming together of two souls in a deep and meaningful relationship. This card reminds you to embrace love, foster emotional connections, and nurture your relationships.

cards.name: Three of Cups
cards.description: An image prompt for the Three of Cups card: Three figures celebrating together, often raising their cups in joy, representing friendship, joy, and community.
cards.interpretation: The Three of Cups represents friendship, joy, and community. It signifies a time of celebration and the nurturing of social connections. This card reminds you to appreciate the support and love of your friends and find joy in shared experiences.

cards.name: Four of Cups
cards.description: An image prompt for the Four of Cups card: A person seated or standing with crossed arms, often looking contemplative or disinterested, representing introspection, contemplation, and apathy.
cards.interpretation: The Four of Cups represents introspection, contemplation, and apathy. It signifies a time of introspection and reevaluation of your emotional state. This card encourages you to examine your feelings and find new perspectives to overcome apathy or dissatisfaction.

cards.name: Five of Cups

cards.interpretation: The Five of Cups represents loss, disappointment, and emotional pain. It signifies a time of grief or regret over past experiences. This card reminds you to acknowledge your emotions, learn from your losses, and find the strength to move forward.

cards.name: Six of Cups

cards.interpretation: The Six of Cups represents nostalgia, innocence, and childhood memories. It signifies a time of revisiting the past or finding joy in simple pleasures. This card encourages you to connect with your inner child and find happiness in nostalgic memories.

cards.name: Seven of Cups

cards.interpretation: The Seven of Cups represents choices, illusions, and desires. It signifies a time of decision-making and the need to discern between fantasy and reality. This card reminds you to prioritize your goals and make choices that align with your true desires.

cards.name: Eight of Cups

cards.interpretation: The Eight of Cups represents introspection, seeking, and moving on. It signifies a time of soul-searching and the need to let go of what no longer serves you. This card encourages you to embark on a spiritual journey and find fulfillment in new experiences.

cards.name: Nine of Cups
cards.description: An image prompt for the Nine of Cups card: A person seated with their arms crossed, often surrounded by nine cups in a state of contentment or satisfaction, representing fulfillment, emotional well-being, and wishes granted.
cards.interpretation: The Nine of Cups represents fulfillment, emotional well-being, and wishes granted. It signifies a time of contentment and satisfaction with your current situation. This card reminds you to count your blessings and appreciate the abundance in your life.

cards.name: Ten of Cups

cards.interpretation: The Ten of Cups represents harmony, love, and emotional fulfillment. It signifies a time of deep emotional connection and domestic bliss. This card reminds you to nurture your relationships and create a harmonious and loving environment.

cards.name: Page of Cups
cards.description: An image prompt for the Page of Cups card: A youthful figure holding a cup, often with a dreamy or imaginative expression, representing creativity, intuition, and emotional exploration.
cards.interpretation: The Page of Cups represents creativity, intuition, and emotional exploration. It signifies the emergence of artistic talents or the development of your intuition. This card encourages you to embrace your imagination and explore your emotions with curiosity.

cards.name: Knight of Cups
cards.description: An image prompt for the Knight of Cups card: A knight figure on a horse, often with a cup, in a romantic or poetic pose, representing romance, passion, and idealism.
cards.interpretation: The Knight of Cups represents romance, passion, and idealism. It signifies a time of emotional intensity and the pursuit of your dreams. This card encourages you to embrace your passions and express your emotions openly and authentically.

cards.name: Queen of Cups
cards.description: An image prompt for the Queen of Cups card: A queen figure seated on a throne, often holding a cup, with a serene and compassionate presence, representing empathy, intuition, and emotional maturity.
cards.interpretation: The Queen of Cups represents empathy, intuition, and emotional maturity. It signifies a time of heightened emotional intelligence and the ability to connect deeply with others. This card reminds you to trust your intuition and lead with compassion in your relationships.

cards.name: King of Cups
cards.description: An image prompt for the King of Cups card: A king figure seated on a throne, often holding a cup, with a calm and compassionate presence, representing emotional balance, wisdom, and control.
cards.interpretation: The King of Cups represents emotional balance, wisdom, and control. It signifies a time of emotional maturity and the ability to navigate complex feelings with grace. This card reminds you to maintain a sense of calm and emotional stability in your life.

cards.name: Ace of Swords
cards.description: An image prompt for the Ace of Swords card: A hand emerging from clouds, holding a sword aloft, often with a crown or wreath, representing clarity, truth, and mental breakthroughs.
cards.interpretation: The Ace of Swords represents clarity, truth, and mental breakthroughs. It signifies a new beginning in your intellectual or communication endeavors. This card encourages you to seek truth, speak your mind, and embrace mental clarity.

cards.name: Two of Swords
cards.description: An image prompt for the Two of Swords card: A person seated, blindfolded, and holding two crossed swords, representing indecision, stalemate, and the need for balance.
cards.interpretation: The Two of Swords represents indecision, stalemate, and the need for balance. It signifies a period of weighing options and finding a middle ground. This card reminds you to trust your intuition and seek a harmonious resolution.

cards.name: Three of Swords
cards.description: An image prompt for the Three of Swords card: Three swords piercing a heart, often depicted against a stormy background, representing heartbreak, sorrow, and emotional pain.
cards.interpretation: The Three of Swords represents heartbreak, sorrow, and emotional pain. It signifies a time of grief and the need to process difficult emotions. This card reminds you to take time to heal and seek support from loved ones.

cards.name: Four of Swords

cards.interpretation: The Four of Swords represents solitude, rest, and recuperation. It signifies a time of pause and self-reflection. This card encourages you to take a break, recharge your energy, and find inner peace.

cards.name: Five of Swords

cards.interpretation: The Five of Swords represents conflict, loss, and betrayal. It signifies a challenging situation where winning may come at a cost. This card reminds you to choose your battles wisely and consider the long-term consequences of your actions.

cards.name: Six of Swords
cards.description: An image prompt for the Six of Swords card: A person and sometimes others in a boat, often depicted traveling away from a turbulent or challenging situation, representing transition, healing, and moving on.
cards.interpretation: The Six of Swords represents transition, healing, and moving on. It signifies a journey away from a difficult situation toward calmer waters. This card encourages you to embrace change, seek healing, and trust in the process of transformation.

cards.name: Seven of Swords

cards.interpretation: The Seven of Swords represents deception, trickery, and stealth. It signifies a situation where someone may not have your best interests at heart. This card reminds you to be cautious and trust your instincts to protect yourself from potential harm.

cards.name: Eight of Swords

cards.interpretation: The Eight of Swords represents self-imposed limitations, restriction, and powerlessness. It signifies a situation where you may feel trapped or unable to see the possibilities before you. This card reminds you to examine your beliefs and break free from self-imposed limitations.

cards.name: Nine of Swords

cards.interpretation: The Nine of Swords represents anxiety, worry, and sleepless nights. It signifies a time of mental distress and overthinking. This card reminds you to seek support, practice self-care, and find healthy ways to cope with your worries.

cards.name: Ten of Swords

cards.interpretation: The Ten of Swords represents pain, betrayal, and the end of a difficult situation. It signifies a time of deep wounds and the need to let go of past pain. This card reminds you that even in the darkest moments, there is always the potential for new beginnings.

cards.name: Page of Swords

cards.interpretation: The Page of Swords represents curiosity, intellectual growth, and new ideas. It signifies the emergence of fresh perspectives and the pursuit of knowledge. This card encourages you to be open-minded, embrace learning opportunities, and express your thoughts with confidence.

cards.description: An image prompt for the Knight of Pentacles card: A knight figure on a stationary horse, often holding a pentacle or coin, with a steadfast or cautious expression, representing responsibility, reliability, and methodical progress.
cards.interpretation: The Knight of Pentacles represents responsibility, reliability, and methodical progress. It signifies a time of diligent work and a steady approach to achieving your goals. This card reminds you to stay committed, take calculated risks, and embrace a patient and thorough mindset to achieve lasting success.

cards.name: Queen of Pentacles
cards.description: An image prompt for the Queen of Pentacles card: A queen figure seated on a throne, often surrounded by nature or holding a pentacle or coin, representing abundance, nurturing, and practicality.
cards.interpretation: The Queen of Pentacles represents abundance, nurturing, and practicality. It signifies a time of stability and nurturing others with a generous spirit. This card reminds you to create a harmonious home environment, cultivate self-care practices, and use your resources wisely to support those around you.

cards.name: King of Pentacles
cards.description: An image prompt for the King of Pentacles card: A king figure seated on a throne, often surrounded by wealth or holding a pentacle or coin, representing abundance, financial mastery, and prosperity.
cards.interpretation: The King of Pentacles represents abundance, financial mastery, and prosperity. It signifies a time of material success and the wise management of resources. This card reminds you to embrace your power as a provider and take a responsible and practical approach to your financial affairs.
